<paragraph id="8E22F219421D256735F5D54AFDCBFABF" blockId="4.[151,620,1309,1335]" box="[151,620,1309,1335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<heading id="D56A4575421D256735F5D54AFDCBFABF" bold="true" box="[151,620,1309,1335]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BCE92E0B421D256735F5D54AFDCBFABF" bold="true" box="[151,620,1309,1335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="499D899A421D256735F5D54AFE1DFABF" box="[151,442,1309,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pearstonensis">
<emphasis id="BCE92E0B421D256735F5D54AFE1DFABF" bold="true" box="[151,442,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Patellapis pearstonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E22F219421D256735F5D532FDFFF99C" blockId="4.[151,1437,1381,1556]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
Males are characterised by a sparse row of 
<number id="3855E03E421D256737C0D532FD7AFAF7" box="[674,733,1381,1407]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" value="9.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="6.0">6–12</number>
usually strong, long, curled and erect bristles on posterior margin of S 
<number id="3855E03E421D25673444D5DDFE9FFA2C" box="[294,312,1418,1444]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
. Usually, the females of the 
<taxonomicName id="499D899A421D256737EDD5DCFCF5FA2C" box="[655,850,1419,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pearstonensis">
<emphasis id="BCE92E0B421D256737EDD5DCFCF5FA2C" box="[655,850,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. pearstonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group have reddish coloured metasomal terga (at least T 
<number id="3855E03E421D25673439D5E7FECDFA42" box="[347,362,1456,1482]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
–T 
<number id="3855E03E421D256734ECD5E7FE3AFA42" box="[398,413,1456,1482]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
) and / or a coarsely punctated clypeus and a strongly reticulate supraclypeal area. Further, their inner hind tibial spur is often strongly serrate (about 
<number id="3855E03E421D256736DFD582FC4CFA67" box="[957,1003,1493,1519]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
long, oblique projections) and their scutal surface is completely reticulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
